**PRIVACY POLICY**
*Last updated July 05, 2025*

Welcome to **Ambigram** (“**Ambigram**,” “**we**,” “**us**” or “**our**”).  This Privacy Policy explains how and why we collect, store, use and share (“**process**”) your information when you:

* download and use the **Ambigram** mobile application (the “**App**”);
* visit any website or landing page that links to this Privacy Policy; or
* engage with us in any related way, including sales, marketing or events.

If you do not agree with our practices, please do not use the App.
Questions? Contact us at **[privacy@ambigram.app](mailto:privacy@ambigram.app)**.

---

## 1.  INFORMATION WE COLLECT

### Personal information you provide to us

| Category               | Examples                                                                                                                           | Purpose                                              |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| **Identifiers**        | Name (optional), e-mail address, Google/Apple ID, or similar account credentials if you create an account or contact us            | Account creation, support, communication             |
| **User Content**       | Ambigram designs you create, images you import or export, background choices, comments or feedback you submit                      | Provide the core service; enable sharing/downloading |
| **Device Permissions** | Storage (to save images), Photos/Media (to import backgrounds or save exports), Push-notification token (to send tips, reminders)  | Enable expected functionality                        |
| **Usage Data**         | In-app interactions, feature use, crash logs, and diagnostics (collected via Firebase Crashlytics & Google Analytics for Firebase) | App stability, analytics and improvement             |
| **Advertising Data**   | Google AdMob advertising identifier and coarse location (derived from IP), if you view ads in the free tier                        | Ad delivery, frequency capping, fraud prevention     |

We do **not** collect sensitive personal information (e.g., race, religion, sexual orientation, biometric data) and we do **not** ask children under 13 (or the minimum age in your jurisdiction) to use the App.

---

## 2.  HOW WE PROCESS YOUR INFORMATION

1. **Provide & maintain the App** – create ambigrams, render previews, store designs locally or in your cloud backup.
2. **Improve & develop new features** – analyze aggregated usage data to understand which tools people love (or don’t).
3. **Personalise your experience** – remember preferred font presets, color themes or recent designs.
4. **Marketing & communication** – send occasional product updates, only with your consent.
5. **Security & fraud prevention** – detect spam, abuse or unauthorised ad clicks.
6. **Legal compliance** – comply with tax, audit and other statutory obligations.

We rely on the following legal bases: **(a) Contract** (to deliver the App you requested); **(b) Legitimate interests** (improve security, analytics); **(c) Consent** (for marketing push notifications); and **(d) Legal obligation** (when regulators require).

---

## 3.  SHARING YOUR INFORMATION

We only share information:

| Recipient type         | Reason / example                                                                                                 |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Service providers**  | Firebase (hosting, analytics, crash reports), Google AdMob (ad serving), RevenueCat (in-app purchase validation) |
| **Business transfers** | If we merge, sell or transfer assets, your data may move as part of the transaction (we’ll notify you).          |
| **Legal / safety**     | Where required by law, court order or to protect someone’s vital interests.                                      |

We **never** sell your personal information.

---

## 4.  COOKIES & TRACKING

The App itself does not use browser cookies, but third-party SDKs (Firebase, AdMob) set mobile identifiers or similar tracking technologies for analytics and advertising. You can reset or limit these identifiers in your device settings.

---

## 5.  DATA RETENTION

We keep personal data only as long as necessary:

* **Account & design data** – until you delete it in-app or request deletion.
* **Analytics & crash logs** – 24 months (default Firebase retention) then aggregated or deleted.
* **Legal records** – as long as laws require (e.g., tax invoices up to 7 years).

When data is no longer needed we delete or anonymise it.

---

## 6.  CHILDREN’S PRIVACY

Ambigram is **not directed to children under 13**.  We do not knowingly collect data from minors.  If you believe we have done so inadvertently, please contact us and we will delete it.

---

## 7.  YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS

Depending on your location, you can:

* Request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.
* Ask us to correct, delete or restrict processing of your data.
* Object to certain processing (e.g., direct marketing).
* Withdraw consent at any time (this won’t affect prior lawful processing).

To exercise any right, e-mail **[privacy@ambigram.app](mailto:privacy@ambigram.app)** or use the in-app “Privacy & Data” form.  We will respond within 30 days (or the timeframe required by law).

---

## 8.  DO-NOT-TRACK

Because there is no uniform industry DNT standard, we currently do not respond to DNT signals.

---

## 9.  CHANGES TO THIS POLICY

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.  We will post the new version in-app and change the “Last updated” date.  Material changes will be announced via an in-app notice or e-mail.

---

